text: Catherine Ann Warner (born 14 July 1948) is an Australian lawyer and politician. She was the 28th Governor of Tasmania from 10 December 2014 until 9 June 2021. Warner was born in Hobart. She replaced Peter Underwood. In January 2019, Warner was diagnosed with non-Hodgkin lymphoma. ==References== Category:1948 births Category:Living people Category:Governors of Tasmania Category:Politicians from Hobart
